   "body" : "This PR adds compile-time checking for negative locking requirements that follow from the run-time locking requirement `AssertLockNotHeld(cs_main)` in `LimitValidationInterfaceQueue(...)`.\r\n\r\nChanges:\r\n* Add `LOCKS_EXCLUDED(cs_main)` to `LimitValidationInterfaceQueue(...)` which does `AssertLockNotHeld(cs_main)`\r\n* Add `LOCKS_EXCLUDED(cs_main)` to `CChainState::ActivateBestChain(â¦)`, `CChainState:: InvalidateBlock(â¦)` and `CChainState::RewindBlockIndex(â¦)` which all call `LimitValidationInterfaceQueue(...)` which does `AssertLockNotHeld(cs_main)`\r\n* Add `LOCKS_EXCLUDED(cs_main)` to `InvalidateBlock(â¦)` which calls `CChainState::InvalidateBlock(...)` which in turn calls `LimitValidationInterfaceQueue(...)` which  does `AssertLockNotHeld(cs_main)`\r\n* Add `LOCKS_EXCLUDED(cs_main)` to `RewindBlockIndex(â¦)` which calls `CChainState::RewindBlockIndex(...)` which in turn calls `LimitValidationInterfaceQueue(...)` which does `AssertLockNotHeld(cs_main)`",
